This is the README file for gitload.

Description:
This package provides a script that needs to be sourced in the user's shell environment.

Installation:
1. Install the package using dpkg: sudo dpkg -i mypackage.deb
2. Source the script in your shell configuration file:
   echo 'source /etc/profile.d/gitload.sh' >> ~/.bashrc
   echo 'source /etc/profile.d/gitload.sh' >> ~/.zshrc
3. Reload your shell configuration:
   source ~/.bashrc
   source ~/.zshrc

Usage:
After installation and sourcing the script, you can use the gitload command in your shell.
